### Step 5: Create query to fetch products

Form for entering data is ready, now you need a way to fetch them from the database. You should create a generic query that will be reused throughout the app to fetch lists of products.

#### marketplace_builder/graph_queries/product/get_products.graphql

```graphql
query get_products($id: ID) {
  customizations(id: $id, name: "product") {
    results {
      id
      name: property(name: "name")
      description: property(name: "description")
      price: property(name: "price")
      brand: model(join_on_property: "brand_id") {
        name: property(name: "name")
      }
      product_type: model(join_on_property: "product_type_id") {
        name: property(name: "name")
      }
    }
  }
}
```

Initially, query will have only one parameter `$id`, but in the future articles you’ll extend it with different filters to implement filtering, pagination etc.

